<div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
      		
	<p n="1">
		Prosperity! Fortune!
	</p>
	
	<p n="1-3">
		Sixteenth year of the victorious king Dantivarmaṉ<note>Tantiparumaṉ, in the original spelling.</note>.
	</p>
	
	<p n="3-12">
		The people <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kuṭi</foreign></supplied> that Kuvāvaṉ Cāttaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Viṭēlviṭuku Muttaraiyaṉ assigned <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaitta</foreign><note>Literally, "endowed", "gave".</note></supplied> so as to supply oil for a glorious lamp for the god <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>paṭārar</foreign></supplied> of Tiruvalattūr <supplied reason="subaudible">are</supplied>:
		Māyāṉ Kāṭaṉ,
		Māyāṉ villi,
		<gap reason="ellipsis"/>,
		<gap reason="ellipsis"/>,
		our relatives,
		Nakkaṉ Koṇai,
		Nakkaṉ <gap reason="ellipsis"/>.		
	</p>
	
</div>
      	
